    • Method Detail

      • getFromMethod

        public static <T,​R> T getFromMethod​(java.lang.reflect.Method m,
                                          java.lang.Class<R> annotationToFind,
                                          java.lang.Object[] invocationParams,
                                          java.util.function.BiFunction<java.lang.reflect.Parameter[],​java.lang.Object[],​T> howToGet)
        Returns desired object using signature of an invoked Method, values of parameters of current invocation of the method and type of annotation that should mark parameters of the method.
        Type Parameters:
        T - is a type of resulted objects
        R - is type of annotation that is expected to mark parameters of the method
        Parameters:
        m - is an invoked method of HttpAPI
        annotationToFind - is type of annotation that is expected to mark any parameters of the method
        invocationParams - is an array of parameters of current invocation of the method
        howToGet - is a bi-function that describes how to get desired result. Here Parameter[] is an array of parameters annotated by annotationToFind and Object[] is an array of corresponding objects taken from the invocationParams
        Returns:
        T if there are parameters annotated by annotationToFind. null is returned otherwise.
